Allow us to (re)introduce ourselves??

Do you want to change how the AMS is run, want to fund a new initiative on campus, or donít like a particular student fee you are paying? If that interests you, why not try to run a referendum in this yearís AMS Elections. Anyone can petition for a referendum, and referendums can levy new AMS student fees, eliminate or change current AMS student fees, amend the AMS bylaws or constitution, and so much more. If you think you can gather over 1000 student signatures to support your referendum reach out to elections@ams.ubc.ca to start your petition now. If you want to petition for a referendum, read more about the process in our AMS Referendum Guide (link in bio).

Students who are assessed AMS Fees this term can apply to opt-out of paying certain AMS Fees. The opt-out form is available from now to January 22 at 11:59PM. In addition, if you're a new student starting in term 2 and already have extended Health and Dental coverage, you can choose to opt-out of the AMS Health and Dental Plan within the change of coverage period, which is from now till January 24, 2024 11:59PM. For more information and the links to the relevant forms, please visit ams.ubc.ca/optout

The AMS Fee and SUB Renewal Fee subsidy is available for new students starting in term 2 who have been assessed AMS Fees. The application form is available from now till January 19 at 11:59PM. The U-Pass subsidy is now open for application to students who are assessed U-Pass fess. The application form is available from now till February 5 at 11:59PM.

Happy New Year! This morning, AMS President Ben Du welcomed Shadan, the first Blue Chip Customer of 2024 with a brand-new AMS Gift Card to start the new year. Wishing everyone a happy new year filled with warm treats and delicious drinks! Heads up, weíve got a new gift card system! If youíre looking to buy one, please inquire at the AMS office on the 3rd floor of the Nest. If you have an old AMS gift card with money still on it, you can transfer the balance to a new card. Please email tomcoleman@ams.ubc.ca with your full name, email address, phone number and a photo of the back of the old card.
If this is your first term of the 2023W academic year, your Opt-Out and Change-of-Coverage period is January 3rd to 24th. Visit the link in our bio for more info!
